WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:05.239
[ Duck quacks, wind whistles ]

00:05.273 --> 00:06.907
[ Zaps ]

00:08.376 --> 00:09.910
[ Roars ]

00:13.747 --> 00:16.350
♪ Adventure time,
come on, grab your friends ♪

00:16.384 --> 00:19.153
♪ We'll go to
very messed up lands ♪

00:19.187 --> 00:21.389
♪ With Finn and Jake,
Ice King, and Betty ♪

00:21.422 --> 00:23.157
♪ Who knows how it will end?

00:23.191 --> 00:25.526
♪ It's adventure time

00:33.801 --> 00:35.035
[ Ship horn blows ]

00:35.069 --> 00:36.870
Jake: Heck, yeah!
We're home.

00:36.904 --> 00:38.106
That was definitely

00:38.139 --> 00:40.208
the longest adventure
we've ever done.

00:40.241 --> 00:41.942
What about when you got trapped
in a mind dungeon

00:41.975 --> 00:43.444
for a buncha years?

00:43.477 --> 00:45.913
This trip was longer
in emotional time.

00:45.946 --> 00:49.550
Yeah, I'm burnt out. No more
adventures for a while, okay?

00:49.583 --> 00:52.453
Yes! Yes! Yes!

00:52.486 --> 00:54.922
[ Babbles loudly ]
B-b-b-b-b-b-b!

00:54.955 --> 00:56.390
Let's go take hot showers.

00:56.424 --> 00:58.959
Hey, look at this fish.

00:58.992 --> 01:00.194
[ Squish ]

01:00.228 --> 01:02.130
It's...gummy?

01:02.163 --> 01:03.531
[ High-pitched voice ]
Hello!

01:03.564 --> 01:06.100
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!
Hey!

01:06.134 --> 01:09.203
[ Laughing ]

01:09.237 --> 01:10.871
Well, that's weird.

01:10.904 --> 01:12.773
We should defs check it out
after we hit up the tree house.

01:12.806 --> 01:16.510
Yeah, we gotta get to the bottom
of this hot shower.

01:22.483 --> 01:23.584
Hmm.

01:23.617 --> 01:25.953
Does everything seem...
pinker to you?

01:25.986 --> 01:28.422
Home always looks different
after a long trip.

01:28.456 --> 01:30.958
You're seeing it with fresh eyes
and newfound wisdom.

01:30.991 --> 01:33.794
And sometimes there's also
a new strip mall or something.

01:33.827 --> 01:35.929
So everything being pink is
probably not a big deal.

01:35.963 --> 01:38.132
And also, I'm tired.

01:38.166 --> 01:39.600
I like the pink.

01:39.633 --> 01:42.436
Why you worry so much,
worry baby?

01:42.470 --> 01:45.806
Ha, ha, yeah! Why you worry
so much, worry baby?

01:45.839 --> 01:47.175
Don't worry, Finn.

01:47.208 --> 01:50.110
We're only teasing you
because you're a baby.

01:50.144 --> 01:51.779
Whoa!

01:51.812 --> 01:54.815
What the heck happened
to the tree house?

01:57.951 --> 01:59.187
Candy...

01:59.220 --> 02:00.621
Fern?

02:00.654 --> 02:02.790
[ Squish ]

02:02.823 --> 02:04.958
[ Dripping ]

02:04.992 --> 02:07.761
Oh, I do not like this.

02:07.795 --> 02:11.999
♪♪

02:12.032 --> 02:14.802
Is this some kind of sick joke?

02:14.835 --> 02:17.805
Because I love it!

02:17.838 --> 02:19.473
Finn: Huh?

02:19.507 --> 02:22.976
Big Baby root beer?
No one buys this brand.

02:23.010 --> 02:24.978
It's too sweet.

02:25.012 --> 02:26.280
Hello?

02:26.314 --> 02:27.815
[ Both gasp ]

02:27.848 --> 02:29.183
Aah!

02:29.217 --> 02:31.151
Hey! You look like me!

02:31.185 --> 02:32.386
Fern?!

02:32.420 --> 02:36.056
Who's Fern? I'm Fun the Human.

02:36.089 --> 02:39.627
And I'm Nectr,
the little robot!

02:39.660 --> 02:43.130
I'm Shelby the Worm...
the gummy worm!

02:43.163 --> 02:44.732
Welcome, strangers.

02:44.765 --> 02:47.201
It's so cool that you're
inside our house.

02:47.235 --> 02:49.537
Dude, when did you guys
turn into candy?

02:49.570 --> 02:54.342
We've always been candy,
you silly billy bean!

02:54.375 --> 02:56.244
Ohh, okay. I get it.

02:56.277 --> 02:58.712
We've obviously stumbled into
another alternate dimension

02:58.746 --> 03:01.715
where everyone's a different
version of themselves.

03:01.749 --> 03:03.517
Yawn.

03:03.551 --> 03:06.220
But we haven't gone through
any portals.

03:06.254 --> 03:07.721
BMO would know.

03:07.755 --> 03:09.022
Hello!

03:09.056 --> 03:10.524
Neptr is so cute now!

03:10.558 --> 03:12.726
I'm going to start treating him
as an equal.

03:12.760 --> 03:15.529
You were supposed to take care
of Ooo while I was gone.

03:15.563 --> 03:17.197
What happened with that?

03:17.231 --> 03:18.566
What?

03:18.599 --> 03:21.034
You used to be this volatile
plant boy. Remember?

03:21.068 --> 03:23.671
Really? Well, I'm candy now.

03:23.704 --> 03:26.340
And I'm in control
of my emotions.

03:26.374 --> 03:27.875
I'm in control, too...

03:27.908 --> 03:29.277
of my body!

03:29.310 --> 03:30.711
[ Laughs ]

03:30.744 --> 03:32.546
Wow, gummy Shelby's
a lot of fun.

03:32.580 --> 03:35.082
I think I'm okay with
Candyworld.

03:35.115 --> 03:37.551
No way. Let's talk to PB.

03:37.585 --> 03:40.220
I'm sure this is all one
of her experiments gone wrong.

03:40.254 --> 03:42.222
You seem upset, friend.

03:42.256 --> 03:45.225
The tower will fix you right up.

03:45.259 --> 03:46.760
The what now?

03:46.794 --> 03:48.061
[ Gulping ]

03:48.095 --> 03:50.097
[ Bell dinging ]
Oh, boy!

03:50.130 --> 03:52.400
Let's run outside!

03:52.433 --> 03:55.403
[ Bell dinging continues ]
[ Nectr whirring ]

03:55.436 --> 03:58.939
[ Wheels squeaking ]

04:03.076 --> 04:05.313
Hello! It's me!

04:05.346 --> 04:06.914
Lemonpink!

04:06.947 --> 04:08.582
He was inside the lemon.

04:08.616 --> 04:10.818
Mm! Drink up, babies!

04:10.851 --> 04:12.786
[ Splat ]
Squeeze!

04:12.820 --> 04:14.455
[ Laughing ]

04:14.488 --> 04:17.157
I used to have a lot of fear
and sadness,

04:17.190 --> 04:20.394
but now I'm fine!

04:20.428 --> 04:21.729
Hey, I want some of that.

04:21.762 --> 04:24.164
No. That is body juice.

04:24.197 --> 04:27.100
Hmm? What's that?

04:27.134 --> 04:30.103
Do you spurn my fluids?

04:30.137 --> 04:31.472
No.

04:31.505 --> 04:34.842
Maybe someone's feeling
a little sour!

04:34.875 --> 04:36.310
Wuh-whoa!

04:36.344 --> 04:38.412
You know what sours get.

04:38.446 --> 04:40.113
Sours get the tower!

04:40.147 --> 04:43.317
Candies: Sours get the tower!
Sours get the tower!

04:43.351 --> 04:47.455
[ Splat ]
Sours get the tower!
Sours get the tower!

04:47.488 --> 04:49.957
Come on, Jake.
Let's go see Bubblegum.

04:49.990 --> 04:52.693
[ Screaming ]

04:55.663 --> 04:58.466
Stop striding!
It just keeps you agitated!

04:58.499 --> 05:01.835
I'm freaking out, Jake.
This place is weird.

05:03.036 --> 05:05.773
What I'm hearing is
you're stressed out

05:05.806 --> 05:08.108
because everything's candy.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.309
Aren't you?

05:09.343 --> 05:10.978
Not really.

05:11.011 --> 05:12.613
Lemongrab's always been
a weirdo.

05:12.646 --> 05:14.314
At least now
he's helping people.

05:14.348 --> 05:17.317
[ Rumbling ]
And Fern is, like,
laughing and joking around.

05:17.351 --> 05:20.821
Maybe they don't need you
to fix them.

05:20.854 --> 05:22.155
Hmm.

05:22.189 --> 05:24.658
I always believe you when
you use that voice.

05:24.692 --> 05:28.161
[ Crying in distance ]

05:28.195 --> 05:31.799
[ Crying continues ]

05:31.832 --> 05:33.300
Sweet P?

05:33.333 --> 05:35.503
[ Sniffles ]

05:35.536 --> 05:38.872
Hey, buddy, what are you
doing out...uh...

05:38.906 --> 05:41.475
Hey! You're meat!

05:41.509 --> 05:43.844
Yes, I'm meat. [ Sniffles ]

05:43.877 --> 05:46.380
But everything else is weird.

05:46.414 --> 05:50.751
Wow, Sweet P, that's almost
exactly what I've been saying.

05:50.784 --> 05:53.687
Sweet P, do you remember
what happened?

05:53.721 --> 05:55.389
One day, the candy came

05:55.423 --> 05:59.760
and turned Mommy and Daddy
into something...different.

05:59.793 --> 06:03.531
Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig:
Sweet P!

06:03.564 --> 06:04.898
There you are!

06:04.932 --> 06:08.502
We've been looking for you
everywhere!

06:08.536 --> 06:10.671
We just love ya
so much, son.

06:10.704 --> 06:13.340
You're gonna get into
a great college!

06:13.373 --> 06:16.844
Tee-hee-hee-hee!
Tee-hee-hee!

06:16.877 --> 06:20.047
They look so happy,
like dogs.

06:20.080 --> 06:21.381
Don't worry, Sweet P.

06:21.415 --> 06:22.850
We're headed
to the Candy Kingdom

06:22.883 --> 06:24.852
to see Princess Bubblegum
about all this.

06:24.885 --> 06:27.387
She's not in the Candy Kingdom.

06:27.421 --> 06:30.891
She's in the Terrible Tower.

06:30.924 --> 06:33.160
Look!

06:35.729 --> 06:38.265
Come on, Jake.
That's kind of weird, right?

06:38.298 --> 06:40.468
I think it's magnificent!

06:40.501 --> 06:44.237
Sweet P! Yoo-hoo!

06:44.271 --> 06:46.039
We brought some rollers

06:46.073 --> 06:49.577
and a bucket
of sweet juicy caramel.

06:49.610 --> 06:52.746
Let's get you back to normal.

06:52.780 --> 06:56.216
But, Mama, I am normal!

06:56.249 --> 07:00.588
Just sit tight there
like a windowpane,

07:00.621 --> 07:04.658
and you'll be back to normal
like a windowpane.

07:04.692 --> 07:07.795
[ Echoing ] Back to normal.

07:07.828 --> 07:11.231
Hmm. Okay, you're right.
This is pretty freaky-deaky.

07:11.264 --> 07:14.602
I'm gonna go now. [ Crying ]

07:14.635 --> 07:16.436
Jake and Finn:
Sweet P, come back!

07:16.470 --> 07:19.306
[ Tree Trunks laughs ]

07:19.339 --> 07:22.610
Uh...let's get to the tower.

07:22.643 --> 07:24.778
♪♪

07:24.812 --> 07:27.114
And never be
the guy with no phone, Finn.

07:27.147 --> 07:29.282
You'll think it'll make people
wanna talk to you more,

07:29.316 --> 07:32.019
but people just forget
to invite you to things.

07:32.052 --> 07:33.420
You've convinced me.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.988
Plus, I like
late night bedtime calls

07:35.022 --> 07:37.991
when you're sleeping over
at Lady's.

07:38.025 --> 07:39.259
[ Sniffs ]

07:39.292 --> 07:40.994
Ooh. Somethin' smells nice.

07:41.028 --> 07:43.964
Nice and toasty.

07:43.997 --> 07:45.365
[ Roars ]

07:45.398 --> 07:46.634
All: S'more!

07:46.667 --> 07:48.168
Stay back, S'more!

07:48.201 --> 07:49.670
Jake: Get it! Get it!
Get it! Get it!

07:49.703 --> 07:53.006
[ Growls ]
[ Laughs ] Whoa, dudes.

07:54.508 --> 07:56.209
I was just playin'.

07:56.243 --> 07:58.712
All: What?! Marceline!

07:58.746 --> 08:02.149
[ Giggles ]
No, it's Marshmaline...

08:02.182 --> 08:04.051
the Campfire Queen.

08:04.084 --> 08:05.318
Mar--
Marsha--

08:05.352 --> 08:06.520
Marsha-- Mars--
Marsha --

08:06.554 --> 08:07.788
Marcine.
Mar-- Mar--

08:07.821 --> 08:09.790
Marsh-- Marshmi--
Marshman-- My--

08:09.823 --> 08:11.324
Would you like to hear a song?

08:11.358 --> 08:13.827
I've written just the ditty
that'll cheer up anyone

08:13.861 --> 08:16.329
that's overwhelmed with work
or responsibility.

08:16.363 --> 08:19.332
Yay! I love Marshmaline songs!

08:19.366 --> 08:22.202
No time for tunes.
Do you know where Bonnie is?

08:22.235 --> 08:25.338
Of course! Follow me.

08:25.372 --> 08:29.810
[ Humming "Greensleeves" ]

08:29.843 --> 08:34.548
[ Humming continues ]

08:36.750 --> 08:40.053
[ Humming ends ]

08:40.087 --> 08:42.823
Marshy...where's PB?

08:42.856 --> 08:45.158
She's everywhere.

08:45.192 --> 08:48.528
[ Rumbling ]

08:48.562 --> 08:51.699
Good tidings to you,
my friends.

08:51.732 --> 08:53.066
[ Gasps ]
[ Gasps ]

08:53.100 --> 08:54.568
Yahoo!

08:54.602 --> 08:56.536
What -- what happened to you?

08:56.570 --> 08:58.205
Oh, this? [ Giggles ]

08:58.238 --> 09:01.208
I've become what I was always
meant to become --

09:01.241 --> 09:04.244
a pure candy elemental.

09:04.277 --> 09:06.246
[ Vomits ]

09:06.279 --> 09:10.350
[ Laughs, cheering ]

09:10.383 --> 09:12.620
[ Belches ] 'Scuse me.

09:12.653 --> 09:14.521
What about Tree Trunks
and Lemongrab

09:14.554 --> 09:16.456
and Marceline
and everyone else?

09:16.489 --> 09:18.592
I fixed 'em, obviously.

09:18.626 --> 09:20.928
Fixed 'em?
But they're your friends!

09:20.961 --> 09:23.631
Those aren't
mutually exclusive concepts.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.398
That means it's fine.

09:25.432 --> 09:27.467
No, it's not fine.

09:27.500 --> 09:28.902
Don't fret.

09:28.936 --> 09:31.204
I can fix you, too.

09:31.238 --> 09:34.207
[ Squishing ]

09:34.241 --> 09:35.743
Aah! Aah! Aah!

09:35.776 --> 09:37.577
I can feel my bones
turning gummy!

09:37.611 --> 09:38.746
Me, too!

09:38.779 --> 09:40.147
We gotta get out of here
before --

09:40.180 --> 09:41.381
Oof!
Hugs!

09:41.414 --> 09:43.250
I'm connected to all candy

09:43.283 --> 09:45.252
throughout all the galaxies.

09:45.285 --> 09:49.923
Once you're candy,
you'll be part of me, too!

09:49.957 --> 09:52.559
No! That plan sucks!

09:52.592 --> 09:53.994
[ Speaking indistinctly ]
Oh, my gosh!

09:54.027 --> 09:56.163
Aah!
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

09:56.196 --> 09:58.398
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
I'm sorry!
Ow!

09:58.431 --> 09:59.599
Skyhooks!

09:59.633 --> 10:02.302
Ice King?

10:02.335 --> 10:04.437
Hold on to me, bro!

10:04.471 --> 10:06.273
No!

10:06.306 --> 10:09.109
Wait, we forgot...BMO!

10:09.142 --> 10:12.179
Goodbye, boys!
It's better this way!

10:12.212 --> 10:13.914
[ Beeping ]

10:13.947 --> 10:17.184
[ Sighs ] Oh, well.
They'll be back.

10:17.217 --> 10:18.418
[ Snaps ]

10:18.451 --> 10:20.788
They have nowhere else to go.

10:20.821 --> 10:24.758
[ Both screaming ]

10:24.792 --> 10:26.459
Yah!
Ooh!

10:26.493 --> 10:28.729
[ Groans ]

10:30.330 --> 10:31.799
Are we in...

10:31.832 --> 10:33.466
Cloud Kingdom.

10:33.500 --> 10:34.868
Looks like we got away

10:34.902 --> 10:37.037
before the candy curse
became permanent.

10:37.070 --> 10:40.307
That's right.
My skyhooks saved the day.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.309
Thanks for getting us out
of there, Simon.

10:42.342 --> 10:46.680
Aw, I can't take all the credit.
It's all thanks to my skyhooks.

10:46.714 --> 10:49.149
Hey, why are you even up here?

10:49.182 --> 10:52.886
We live here now,
me and the skyhooks.

10:52.920 --> 10:56.256
Finn, you gotta see this.

10:58.658 --> 11:00.027
[ Gasps ]

11:00.060 --> 11:01.394
Oh...my...

11:01.428 --> 11:04.331
but...

11:04.364 --> 11:06.266
Ice King: Skyhooks!

11:08.936 --> 11:12.806
♪ Come along with me

11:12.840 --> 11:17.010
♪ And the butterflies and bees
